I don't miss my [[floppy disk|https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Floppy_disk]] days.
They where painful slow, limited in storage, took up too much time & space, and easily damaged or corrupted.
This technology, invented and first commercially available from IBM in 1971,
was critical to the success of the first personal computer,
but by 2006, computers were rarely manufactured with installed floppy disk drives.
As it turns out, though, even in 2020 the
[[Boeing 747-400 still relies on floppies|https://hackaday.com/2020/08/12/floppy-disks-still-used-to-update-747-flight-software/]].

